# AI/ML Development Standards

## Core AI Principles

- Design for explainability and interpretability
- Implement proper data validation and preprocessing
- Handle uncertainty and confidence scoring
- Use appropriate evaluation metrics
- Document model assumptions and limitations
- Plan for model versioning and updates

## Knowledge Management

- Structure knowledge in semantic, searchable formats
- Implement proper indexing for fast retrieval
- Use embeddings for semantic similarity when appropriate
- Handle multilingual content gracefully
- Implement proper knowledge graph relationships
- Cache frequently accessed knowledge

## Data Processing

- Validate all input data before processing
- Handle missing or corrupted data gracefully
- Implement proper data pipelines with error handling
- Use streaming for large datasets
- Implement proper data versioning
- Log data transformations for reproducibility

## Model Integration

- Abstract model interfaces for easy swapping
- Implement proper model loading and caching
- Handle model failures gracefully with fallbacks
- Use async processing for expensive operations
- Implement proper rate limiting for API calls
- Monitor model performance and drift

## Performance Optimization

- Use batch processing where possible
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use connection pooling for external services
- Optimize database queries for knowledge retrieval
- Implement proper pagination for large results
- Use background tasks for heavy processing

## Security & Privacy

- Sanitize all user inputs
- Implement proper access controls for knowledge
- Use encryption for sensitive data
- Audit knowledge access and modifications
- Implement proper data retention policies
- Handle PII appropriately

## Testing AI Components

- Test with diverse datasets
- Implement regression tests for model outputs
- Test edge cases and error conditions
- Mock external AI services in tests
- Test performance under load
- Validate output quality metrics

